#
#  p-ranav/argparse distinctive features:
#    - HEADER-ONLY — single `argparse.hpp` include; no linking
#    - C++17+ TEMPLATED `.get<T>(name)` accessor for type-safe access
#    - LAMBDA-BASED `.action([](const std::string& value) -> T {...})`
#      for inline value transformation/parsing
#    - METHOD-CHAIN BUILDER per argument:
#      `.required()`, `.optional()`, `.default_value(V)`, `.help("X")`,
#      `.action(lambda)`, `.choices({"a", "b"})`, `.scan<'i', int>()`,
#      `.nargs(N)` / `.nargs('+')` / `.nargs('*')` / `.nargs('?')`,
#      `.implicit_value(V)`, `.append()`, `.store_into(&dest)`
#    - PYTHON-LIKE conventions adapted to C++: `add_argument(...)`
#      with positional name OR `-short, --long` flag names; `.nargs('+'/
#      '*'/'?')` quantifier shortcuts (mimics Python argparse)
#    - AUTO-GENERATED HELP TEXT from descriptions
#    - PARSE-ERRORS-AS-EXCEPTIONS — `parse_args` throws
#      `std::runtime_error` on failure; caller wraps in try/catch
